Design Manual

Colour Scheme

The colour palette is a customised version of the default Tailwind CSS colour system. The main neutral colour is Slate, which has been modified to have a richer, bluer hue and is used for backgrounds and text.

The primary accent colour is Blue, used for links, buttons, and highlighting active elements. Orange serves as a secondary accent for filters and notifications. Red is reserved for destructive actions and error states. All customisations can be found in src/app.css.

Font Stacks

The project currently uses the default Tailwind CSS font stacks, as no custom fonts are defined in either tailwind.config.ts or src/app.css.

  • Sans-serif: 'ui-sans-serif', 'system-ui', '-apple-system', 'BlinkMacSystemFont', "Segoe UI", 'Roboto', "Helvetica Neue", 'Arial', "Noto Sans", 'sans-serif', "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol", "Noto Color Emoji"
  • Serif: 'ui-serif', 'Georgia', 'Cambria', "Times New Roman", 'Times', 'serif'
  • Monospace: 'ui-monospace', 'SFMono-Regular', 'Menlo', 'Monaco', 'Consolas', "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", 'monospace'
